#: template-meaning-of-6.php:51
msgid "We are also aware that independent journalism in Malaysia operates under the shadow of laws designed less to protect the public than to protect power from scrutiny — among them Section 233 of the Communications and Multimedia Act 1998, known in practice, and with good reason, as the %s. We publish anyway. A law that exists to punish inconvenient expression is not a law that deserves our silence. It is a law that deserves to be named."
msgstr "Kami juga sedar bahawa kewartawanan bebas di Malaysia beroperasi di bawah bayang-bayang undang-undang yang direka bukan untuk melindungi orang awam tetapi untuk melindungi kuasa daripada penelitian."

#: template-meaning-of-6.php:46
msgid "We are not neutral — neutrality is a convenient fiction used to avoid accountability. We are independent. We operate in Bahasa Melayu because that is where the conversation that matters to us lives, and because language is never merely a vehicle: it is a political choice. We answer to our readers. We are the Sixth Estate."
msgstr "Kami tidak neutral — neutraliti adalah fiksyen mudah yang digunakan untuk mengelak akauntabiliti. Kami bebas. Kami beroperasi dalam Bahasa Melayu kerana di situlah perbualan yang penting bagi kami hidup."

#: template-editorial-policy.php:47
msgid "We believe that the responsibility of media is not merely to convey information, but to build public trust through responsible journalistic practice."
msgstr "Kami percaya bahawa tanggungjawab media bukan sekadar menyampaikan maklumat, tetapi membina kepercayaan awam melalui amalan kewartawanan yang bertanggungjawab."

#: template-meaning-of-6.php:191
msgid "We did not build UP6 Suara Semasa to be comfortable. We built it to be useful. We built it to be honest. We built it to still be standing — and still publishing — when the pressure comes."
msgstr "Kami tidak membina UP6 Suara Semasa untuk keselesaan. Kami membinanya untuk berguna. Kami membinanya untuk jujur."

#: template-meaning-of-6.php:164
msgid "We do not accept the premise that a free press owes the state the benefit of the doubt. The state has lawyers, spokespersons, press secretaries and the full apparatus of official narrative. It does not need our help. The public, which has none of those things, does."
msgstr "Kami tidak menerima premis bahawa akhbar bebas berhutang kepada negara untuk memberi keraguan yang wajar."

#: template-privacy-policy.php:57
msgid "We do not collect identity card numbers, bank account details, or other sensitive information without your explicit consent."
msgstr "Kami tidak mengumpul nombor kad pengenalan, butiran akaun bank, atau maklumat sensitif lain tanpa persetujuan jelas anda."

#: template-corrections.php:59
msgid "We do not issue corrections for matters of editorial judgement, word choice, or differences of opinion. If a report is disputed, we will consider the dispute on its merits and correct only where the record is demonstrably wrong."
msgstr "Kami tidak mengeluarkan pembetulan untuk perkara pertimbangan editorial, pilihan perkataan, atau perbezaan pendapat."

#: template-corrections.php:63
msgid "We do not scrub errors from the public record. The correction notice remains visible permanently alongside the corrected content, so that readers who encountered the original version are aware that it has been updated."
msgstr "Kami tidak menghapuskan kesilapan daripada rekod awam. Notis pembetulan kekal kelihatan secara kekal bersama kandungan yang dibetulkan."

#: template-privacy-policy.php:67
msgid "We do not use your information for direct marketing without your prior consent."
msgstr "Kami tidak menggunakan maklumat anda untuk pemasaran langsung tanpa persetujuan anda terlebih dahulu."

#: template-editorial-policy.php:104
msgid "We exercise particular care when reporting on:"
msgstr "Kami berhati-hati dalam melaporkan isu yang melibatkan:"

#: template-meaning-of-6.php:146
msgid "We give the subjects of our reporting the right of reply. We present competing accounts where they exist and clearly label them as such. We distinguish between what is established and what is alleged. We do not use journalism as a weapon against individuals, and we do not use it as a shield for institutions. Fairness is a method, not a conclusion — and it is never an excuse for cowardice."
msgstr "Kami memberikan subjek pelaporan kami hak untuk menjawab. Kami membentangkan akaun bersaing di mana ia wujud dan melabelkannya dengan jelas."

#: template-disclaimer.php:60
msgid "We have no control over the nature, content, or availability of external websites. We accept no responsibility for any loss or inconvenience that may arise from your use of third-party content or websites reached through links on this portal."
msgstr "Kami tidak mempunyai kawalan ke atas sifat, kandungan, atau ketersediaan laman web luaran."

#: template-about.php:57
msgid "We hold ourselves to the standards set out in our Editorial Policy — accuracy, fairness, editorial independence and transparency in the use of sources. Corrections are published promptly and without reservation. Readers who identify errors are encouraged to write to us."
msgstr "Kami memegang diri kami kepada piawaian yang ditetapkan dalam Polisi Editorial kami — ketepatan, keadilan, kebebasan editorial dan ketelusan dalam penggunaan sumber."

#: template-privacy-policy.php:50
msgid "We may collect the following information when you interact with UP6 Suara Semasa:"
msgstr "Kami mungkin mengumpulkan maklumat berikut apabila anda berinteraksi dengan UP6 Suara Semasa:"

#: template-meaning-of-6.php:153
msgid "We name our sources where we can. Where we cannot, we explain why — not with a vague appeal to confidentiality, but with a specific account of the editorial judgement made. We do not hide our methods, our funding, our ownership or our limitations. Readers who disagree with our judgements are entitled to the information needed to challenge them."
msgstr "Kami menamakan sumber kami di mana kami boleh. Di mana kami tidak boleh, kami jelaskan mengapa."

#: template-editorial-policy.php:115 template-editorial-policy.php:123
msgid "We recognise that a free press is not a courtesy extended by those in power — it is a right exercised in the public interest, regardless of whether that exercise is convenient for the powerful."
msgstr "Kami mengiktiraf bahawa akhbar bebas bukan ihsan yang diberikan oleh mereka yang berkuasa — ia adalah hak yang dilaksanakan demi kepentingan awam."

#: template-privacy-policy.php:112
msgid "We retain your personal information only for as long as necessary to fulfil the purposes stated in this policy, or as required by law. Anonymous analytics data is retained for a maximum period of 26 months."
msgstr "Kami menyimpan maklumat peribadi anda hanya selama yang perlu untuk memenuhi tujuan yang dinyatakan dalam polisi ini."

#: template-privacy-policy.php:90
msgid "We take reasonable technical and organisational measures to protect your personal information from unauthorised access, loss, or disclosure. However, no data transmission over the internet can be guaranteed as fully secure."
msgstr "Kami mengambil langkah teknikal dan organisasi yang munasabah untuk melindungi maklumat peribadi anda daripada akses tanpa kebenaran, kehilangan, atau pendedahan."

#: template-meaning-of-6.php:202
msgid "We verify before we publish. Our word to the reader is the only currency we have, and we do not spend it carelessly."
msgstr "Kami sahkan sebelum kami terbitkan. Kata kami kepada pembaca adalah satu-satunya mata wang yang kami miliki, dan kami tidak membelanjakannya secara cuai."

#: template-meaning-of-6.php:132
msgid "We verify before we publish. We do not treat speed as an excuse for error, or traffic as a justification for speculation. Every claim that carries our name has been interrogated before it is printed — because our word to the reader is the only currency we have, and we do not spend it carelessly."
msgstr "Kami sahkan sebelum kami terbitkan. Kami tidak merawat kelajuan sebagai alasan untuk kesilapan, atau trafik sebagai justifikasi untuk spekulasi."

#: template-contact.php:67
msgid "We welcome questions, tips, corrections, and feedback from readers, sources, and the public. The editorial team reads every message and will respond within three working days."
msgstr "Kami mengalu-alukan soalan, petunjuk, pembetulan, dan maklum balas daripada pembaca, sumber, dan orang awam."

#: template-meaning-of-6.php:163
msgid "We will name custodial deaths. We will report unlawful detention, the abuse of remand powers, and the use of force against civilians as the serious matters they are — not as isolated incidents, not as procedural anomalies, but as events that demand explanation from those responsible. We will not deploy the word alleged to protect institutions that have the full resources of the state at their disposal. We will not kill a story because someone in authority found it inconvenient."
msgstr "Kami akan menamakan kematian dalam tahanan. Kami akan melaporkan penahanan tanpa undang-undang, penyalahgunaan kuasa reman, dan penggunaan kekerasan terhadap orang awam sebagai perkara serius."

#: template-editorial-policy.php:114 template-editorial-policy.php:122
msgid "We will not reveal the identity of confidential sources under pressure from any authority. Journalists working under the UP6 name have the right to protect their sources, and UP6 will provide reasonable support to any journalist who faces legal or institutional pressure as a result of their work for this publication."
msgstr "Kami tidak akan mendedahkan identiti sumber sulit di bawah tekanan daripada mana-mana pihak berkuasa."

#: index.php:63
msgid "Welcome"
msgstr "Selamat Datang"

#: index.php:65
msgid "Welcome to UP6"
msgstr "Selamat Datang ke UP6"

#: template-corrections.php:51
msgid "What We Correct"
msgstr "Apa Yang Kami Betulkan"

#: template-meaning-of-6.php:103
msgid "What connects us to the region. Malaysia does not exist in isolation from ASEAN, from the South China Sea, from the shifting geometries of regional power and the quiet rearrangements of influence that never make the front page. Serantau coverage traces those connections — the ones that matter before anyone admits they matter."
msgstr "Apa yang menghubungkan kita kepada rantau ini. Malaysia tidak wujud secara terasing daripada ASEAN, daripada Laut China Selatan."

#: template-meaning-of-6.php:111
msgid "What moves money and lives. From Bank Negara policy to ringgit volatility to the informal economy that most financial journalism ignores because its subjects do not read Bloomberg. Economic coverage at UP6 is written for readers, not for traders. The question we ask is not what this means for the market. It is what this means for you."
msgstr "Apa yang menggerakkan wang dan kehidupan. Dari dasar Bank Negara kepada turun naik ringgit kepada ekonomi tidak formal."

#: template-meaning-of-6.php:107
msgid "What reaches us from beyond. Geopolitics, conflict, climate, international markets — the world arrives on our doorstep whether we report it or not. We report it, and we report it through Malaysian eyes: not as spectators to history but as people with a stake in how it unfolds."
msgstr "Apa yang sampai kepada kita dari luar. Geopolitik, konflik, iklim, pasaran antarabangsa — dunia tiba di ambang pintu kita sama ada kita melaporkannya atau tidak."

#: includes/theme-options.php:329
msgid "WhatsApp URL"
msgstr "URL WhatsApp"

#: template-corrections.php:49
msgid "When an error is identified — whether by our own team or brought to our attention by a reader — we will correct it. We will not quietly delete or rewrite content. We will not obscure the fact that a correction was made. We will say what was wrong, what the correct information is, and when the correction was published."
msgstr "Apabila kesilapan dikenal pasti — sama ada oleh pasukan kami sendiri atau dimaklumkan oleh pembaca — kami akan membetulkannya."

#: template-meaning-of-6.php:181
msgid "When we are wrong — and we will be wrong, because journalism is a human enterprise — we say so. At the top of the article. In plain language. With the corrected version clearly stated. No buried footnotes. No quiet edits in the dead of night. No passive-voice non-apologies that acknowledge the error while avoiding the embarrassment. Our credibility is not built by never being wrong. It is built by how we behave when we are."
msgstr "Apabila kami salah — dan kami akan salah, kerana kewartawanan adalah usaha manusia — kami mengatakannya. Di bahagian atas artikel. Dalam bahasa yang jelas."

#: template-corrections.php:66
msgid "Where a correction is significant — involving a material factual error, an incorrect identity, a figure with public consequence, or content that may have caused harm — the correction will be handled with additional care:"
msgstr "Apabila pembetulan adalah penting — melibatkan kesilapan fakta material, identiti yang salah, angka dengan akibat awam, atau kandungan yang mungkin menyebabkan kemudaratan — pembetulan akan dikendalikan dengan penjagaan tambahan:"

#: template-disclaimer.php:73
msgid "Where an article has been materially updated after initial publication, this will be noted within the article. The original publication date and the date of update are recorded for transparency."
msgstr "Apabila artikel telah dikemas kini secara material selepas penerbitan awal, ini akan dinyatakan dalam artikel."

#: template-about.php:37
msgid "Who We Are"
msgstr "Siapa Kami"

#: template-meaning-of-6.php:66
msgid "Who opens the paper and does not see their reality — the longhouse with no clean water, the padi farmer whose subsidy was quietly restructured, the fishing community whose sea is being reclaimed — because it does not make for comfortable reading in a lifestyle supplement."
msgstr "Yang membuka akhbar dan tidak melihat realiti mereka — rumah panjang tanpa air bersih, petani padi yang subsidinya secara senyap distrukturkan semula."

#: template-meaning-of-6.php:86
msgid "Who wants, without ideology or agenda, to know what is actually true — what the government actually decided, what the court actually found, what the money was actually spent on — and who deserves journalism that respects that want enough to answer it honestly."
msgstr "Yang ingin, tanpa ideologi atau agenda, untuk mengetahui apa yang sebenarnya benar — apa yang sebenarnya diputuskan oleh kerajaan."

#: template-meaning-of-6.php:70
msgid "Whose economic precarity is abstracted into headline GDP figures and investment corridor announcements, while the actual experience of not being able to afford rent in the city where you work goes unreported because it implies a question no one in power wants asked."
msgstr "Yang prekariti ekonominya diabstrakan menjadi angka KDNK tajuk utama dan pengumuman koridor pelaburan."

#: template-meaning-of-6.php:74
msgid "Whose political consciousness is dismissed as inexperience, whose anger at inherited dysfunction is reframed as ingratitude, and whose engagement with public life is simultaneously demanded and punished when it produces inconvenient conclusions."
msgstr "Yang kesedaran politiknya ditolak sebagai ketiadaan pengalaman, yang kemarahannya terhadap disfungsi yang diwarisi dibingkai semula sebagai tidak bersyukur."

#: functions.php:186
msgid "Widgets here appear on posts and archives. Uses only core WordPress widgets — no plugins needed."
msgstr "Widget di sini dipaparkan pada artikel dan arkib. Hanya menggunakan widget teras WordPress — tiada pemalam diperlukan."

